    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tamarix, also known as salt cedar, is a deciduous, flowering shrub that historically has been used for windbreaks, ornamentals, and erosion control. Tamarix is highly invasive and affects water drainage systems in North America.</Note_Text>
